{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: specimen-eu-lab_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates a FSH Specimen instance conforming to the SpecimenEu profile
    (EU Laboratory Report profile). This resource represents a single physical
    specimen collected from a patient, characterised by its SNOMED CT type
    and the date/time of collection.

    One Specimen instance is typically generated per distinct specimen type
    referenced by the associated ServiceRequest and DiagnosticReport. Multiple
    lab panels that share the same specimen type will share the same Specimen
    instance (deduplication is the caller's responsibility).

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: SpecimenEu
    Canonical : (EU Laboratory Specimen profile, HL7 Europe / IHE XpandH)
    Must-support elements covered:
      type (SNOMED CT code + display), collection.collectedDateTime

  TWO-COLUMN HTML TABLE
    Column 1 — Specimen type display name    (always present)
    Column 2 — Collection date               (always present; formatted d-M-Y)

  CSS CLASS NOTE
    This template uses `hl7__eu__lab__report` as the table CSS class (rather
    than the `hl7__ips` class used by IPS-context templates). This reflects
    the EU Laboratory Report stylesheet, which applies different column widths
    and typography appropriate for lab report rendering in the vi7eti viewer.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌───────────────────┬──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable          │ Type     │ Description                                  │
  ├───────────────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ instanceid        │ string   │ Unique resource id; appended to              │
  │                   │          │ "Instance-Specimen-" to form the FSH         │
  │                   │          │ instance name.                               │
  │ specimen.code     │ string   │ SNOMED CT concept code for the specimen type │
  │                   │          │ (e.g. "122555007" for venous blood specimen).│
  │                   │          │ Used directly in the $sct# code expression. │
  │ specimen.display  │ string   │ Display name for the specimen type; used in  │
  │                   │          │ the FSH type rule and in HTML td 1.          │
  │ specimen.date     │ string   │ ISO 8601 dateTime of specimen collection;    │
  │                   │          │ used as-is in the FSH rule and formatted     │
  │                   │          │ d-M-Y for the HTML pill cell (td 2).         │
  └───────────────────┴──────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  FSH ELEMENTS EMITTED
    * type                        SNOMED CT specimen type code
    * collection.collectedDateTime  ISO 8601 collection date/time

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    $sct — SNOMED CT; code taken from specimen.code (caller-supplied)

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-09-08
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Specimen-" ~ instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: SpecimenEu
Title: "Specimen"
Description: "Specimen"
Usage: #inline

{#
  ── Core specimen data ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Both elements are mandatory on this template: type identifies what was
  collected, collectedDateTime records when it was collected.
  The SNOMED CT code is interpolated directly into the $sct# code expression.
#}
* id                           = "{{ instanceid }}"
* type                         = $sct#{{ specimen.code}} "{{ specimen.display }}"
* collection.collectedDateTime = "{{ specimen.date }}"

{#
  ── HEAD bag: two-column table header ──────────────────────────────────────
  Describes what type of specimen was collected and when.
#}
{{ addHEAD_tr() }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Specimen") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Collection Date") }}
{{ addHEAD_trend() -}}

{#
  ── HTML bag: single data row ───────────────────────────────────────────────
  td 1: Specimen type display name — plain text cell.
  td 2: Collection date — formatted as d-M-Y (e.g. "14-Mar-1978") in a
        non-breaking pill badge via addHTML_tdnb.
#}
{{ addHTML_tr() }}
{{ addHTML_td(specimen.display) }}
{{ addHTML_tdnb(specimen.date|date('d-M-Y')) }}
{{ addHTML_trend() -}}

{#
  ── FHIR narrative ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Both HEAD and HTML bags are flushed inside text.div, producing a complete
  table (header + data row) in the inline FHIR narrative.
  Note: this template uses the hl7__eu__lab__report CSS class rather than
  hl7__ips, as it targets the EU Laboratory Report stylesheet.
#}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div    = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<table class="hl7__eu__lab__report">
{{ emitHEAD() | raw }}
{{ emitHTML() | raw }}
</table>
</div>
"""

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHEAD() | raw }}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHTML() | raw }}
